    {
      "id": "f75b6aedf8a5dc30914498fe54b0a50fb76c3326",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 277,
        "name": "Jodi Levi",
        "email": "jodi.levi@intel.com",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-02-09 18:35:50.000000000",
      "message": "Topic set to \"Abandon\".\n\nThis patch is a candidate to be abandoned because it has been idle for a long time, or may be obsoleted by another patch that has already been landed.  If you think this patch still contains useful changes, please comment in the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "345e5cc362c0598d922dcdde8b21919e73148317",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-02-26 22:40:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(4 comments)\n\nThe problem I see with this patch, as Keith pointed out, is that this would completely serialize object allocation on the MDS.  It probably makes more sense to opportunistically skip a number of OSCs based on the requested stripe count (and assume they are all available) and then drop the spinlock again.  If it turns out that some of the stripes are not available then the allocation of replacements can be handled as an exception as it is done already.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "80a4296c8508094b05c400769f2f18ef958818d0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-02-26 22:50:35.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nI'd be happy to see work on an improved round-robin allocator (see LU-9).\n\nGiven that this patch needs to be totally rewritten for 2.4 and later, I'm going to abandon it.  There is some discussion in LU-977 on how it might be implemented differently.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    }
  ],
